The point I raised Lukaria was a good answer to your question as to whether or not I believed that the Christian religion could be &quot;made up&quot; by a few people. Even you agree that Islam and even Morminism have been &quot;made up&quot; by individuals. Hence, it is not impossible that Christianity was also invented by a group of people. We certainly see that the major religions are created by the inspiration of individuals carried through time by their followers. Right? Why should Christianity be exempt? You see, I have never understood why some Christians are so caught up with needing historical proof to validate their faith. Why would a Christian really care if the bible is just a collection of fairy tales? Isn't the message contained in the pages what's important? /shrugs<br>
